00:32:55.310 --> 00:32:56.610
&gt;&gt; Anne E. McLean: There's a --

00:32:56.610 --> 00:32:58.400
or somebody that had to be
shielded with an umbrella.

00:32:58.400 --> 00:32:59.700
There's this --

00:32:59.700 --> 00:33:01.430
&gt;&gt; Marcy Rosen: That's
a very funny story.

00:33:01.430 --> 00:33:08.590
There was the -- when -- after Mr.
Serkin died, the very beginning,

00:33:08.590 --> 00:33:12.930
there was a -- there was a
trio of artistic directors.

00:33:12.930 --> 00:33:17.240 position:56%
And one of those artistic directors,
who I don't think I'll name,

00:33:18.800 --> 00:33:22.100
they wanted to do away
with the napkin balls.

00:33:22.100 --> 00:33:25.850
It was not something that
he appreciated and he felt

00:33:25.850 --> 00:33:29.600
that he shouldn't have
to be bombarded by this.

00:33:29.600 --> 00:33:35.740
So a napkin free zone was set up
[laughter] in the dining hall,

00:33:35.740 --> 00:33:39.320
it was a -- it was like there
was a row of music stands

00:33:39.320 --> 00:33:42.500
on which there were signs
that said, "Napkin free zone,"

00:33:42.500 --> 00:33:46.760
which is just really like,
asking people to -- to do it.

00:33:46.760 --> 00:33:51.750
And -- and we have this
wonderful librarian, her --

00:33:51.750 --> 00:33:54.140
who's name I can mention,
her name was Shirley Weekly.

00:33:54.140 --> 00:33:59.080
She had been also a fixture, a
Marlboro fixture for 40 years

00:33:59.080 --> 00:34:02.020
and she was also the
librarian at Curtis.

00:34:02.020 --> 00:34:07.840
A lovely lady, she had some -- she
didn't like -- she loved the --

00:34:07.840 --> 00:34:09.800
well, let's say, she didn't
like the napkin balls either,

00:34:09.800 --> 00:34:12.850
so she hadn't eaten in
the dining room for,

00:34:12.850 --> 00:34:16.060
I don't know, 20 years or more.

00:34:16.060 --> 00:34:17.890
She always took her tray and ate

00:34:17.890 --> 00:34:20.570
in another room off the
-- off the dining hall.

00:34:20.570 --> 00:34:26.230
So, this night that -- of this
inaugural napkin free zone,

00:34:26.230 --> 00:34:30.960
Shirley Weekly came back into the
dining hall, thinking she was safe

00:34:30.960 --> 00:34:32.730
and at one point, and I --

00:34:32.730 --> 00:34:35.410
and I believe I know who
engineered the whole thing.

00:34:35.410 --> 00:34:39.260
And I -- as it happens, the
person who -- who was --

00:34:39.260 --> 00:34:42.090
who was initiating this happens
to be a close friend of mine.

00:34:42.090 --> 00:34:46.410
Then I -- it was -- I was not in
favor of this things, but I --

00:34:46.410 --> 00:34:49.350
was sitting and having dinner with
-- with them on that side of the --

00:34:49.350 --> 00:34:52.900
the other side of the barrier.

00:34:52.900 --> 00:34:59.690 position:56%
The entire other side of the room in
unison , got up and threw napkins.

00:34:59.690 --> 00:35:03.850
And Shirley Weekly never at
in the dining hall again.

00:35:03.850 --> 00:35:08.200
